snippet.textDisplay: I currently live in East Nashville 3 blocks from my cousin and her husband/1.5 year old son/dog and a couple of miles from my friends apartment complex in Germantown. Tornado barely missed me but tore off the roof. Missed my cousins house but completely wrecked like 3/4 of the neighborhood, and my friends apartment complex was pretty much completely wrecked. Luckily I’ve yet to hear any news about any friends/family being killed but my prayers go out to those who have lost loved ones. I’ll never forget the flood of 2010, and the tornado we had back in ‘98 when I was just 4. I remember like it was yesterday. I went to spend the day at my dads job in Nashville. He worked on the 20th floor of the building. The tornado literally passed right by his building and shattered the windows and shook the building.

snippet.textDisplay: Guys, it was scary. The warning went off on my phone around 1230am. A few minutes later I heard it come thru. It sounded just like a freight train as they always say. Made it in the bathroom just in time. No damage to the house, but no power and trees down everywhere. There are three big trees around the house and they all fell away from the house. However not everybody was lucky. At this time there are 25 casualties and nearly 40 unaccounted for. Please keep Nashville and the surrounding areas in your prayers as we try to get things back to normal. #PrayForNashville
